nutrition:
  calories: 336 kcal
  fat: 1 g
  saturated fat: 1 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 11 g
  sodium: 5 g
  serving size: 369
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/lamb-stew-5abd192c30006c21e04a2252
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Fusion
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Bring the @water{300%ml} to the boil in a large #saucepan{} over high heat. Stir
in the @Basmati Rice{150%g}. Cover with a lid, lower the heat to a simmer and
cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered)
for another ~{10%minutes}.

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, halve, then remove the core from the @Green Pepper{1} and chop into
2cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When really
hot, add the @Lamb Strips{240%g} and stir-fry until browned all over, ~{3-4%mins}.

> Don't overcook the lamb, you just want to get a good colour on it - we will be
> adding it back to the sauce later on!

Remove from the pan using a #slotted spoon{} (keep the pan).

Return the pan to medium heat, add the pepper (add a splash of oil if the pan is
dry). Cook, stirring, until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the
@Smoked Paprika{1%tsp} and stir-fry for another ~{1%minute}. Stir in the
@Chopped Tomatoes{1%can}, @Water{200%ml}, @Chicken Stock Powder{1%pot}, and
@?sugar{pinch}. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low. Cook
until thick and tomatoey, stirring occasionally, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add the lamb back into the sauce and heat through for ~{1-2%mins}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and serve in bowls. Spoon the lamb stew on top
of the rice. Enjoy!